{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "COP2/max", "context": "out", "type": "node", "internal": "take_merge_ql", "version": "1", "namespace": "qLib"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Take Merge qL"], "extent": [43, 61]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["interface version 1"]}], "extent": [61, 85]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Merges specified takes together into a (temporary) new take, then renders the result."], "extent": [85, 178]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The takeMerge ROP merges all the specified takes together, then calls the specified\noutput driver."], "extent": [178, 278]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["It allows you to work around the hierarchical nature of takes: they will behave\nmore like 'tags' or 'labels' (or 'overrides' in other applications)."], "extent": [278, 428]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Examples of\u2026"], "extent": [428, 444]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["\u2026what can be stored in takes"], "extent": [444, 476], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["render layer settings (object flags) (say ", {"type": "em", "text": ["character"]}, ", ", {"type": "em", "text": ["background"]}, ")"], "extent": [476, 551]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["settings for single-frame mplay or output image sequence (say ", {"type": "em", "text": ["singleframe"]}, ", ", {"type": "em", "text": ["sequence"]}, ")"], "extent": [551, 646]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["render quality settings (say ", {"type": "em", "text": ["draft"]}, ", ", {"type": "em", "text": ["production"]}, ")"], "extent": [646, 705]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["\u2026how do you combine (merge) them"], "extent": [705, 741], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["'", {"type": "em", "text": ["draft"]}, " ", {"type": "em", "text": ["singleframe"]}, "' to get a quick render of the scene"], "extent": [741, 806]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["'", {"type": "em", "text": ["production"]}, " ", {"type": "em", "text": ["character"]}, " ", {"type": "em", "text": ["singleframe"]}, "' to get a production-quality single frame render of the character"], "extent": [806, 918]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["'", {"type": "em", "text": ["draft"]}, " ", {"type": "em", "text": ["background"]}, " ", {"type": "em", "text": ["sequence"]}, "' to get a rough-quality image sequence of the background layer"], "extent": [918, 1021]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["With regular hierarchical takes all of the above is much harder to achieve."], "extent": [1021, 1100]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["Parameters"], "role": "section", "extent": [1100, 1123], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["HQueue Mode"], "extent": [1123, 1137], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable this if the resulting render will be distributed using HQueue.\n    (see ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Usage with HQueue"]}, " below for instructions)."], "extent": [1137, 1266]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Merged Take Name"], "extent": [1266, 1284], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The name of the new take (the merge result) that will be rendered."], "extent": [1284, 1356]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The default settings is to inherit the name of the node,\n    as it is recommended to ", {"type": "em", "text": ["give each takeMerge node the name of the render layer it represents"]}, "."], "extent": [1356, 1517]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This take is temporary: it exists only during render and gets deleted on completion."], "extent": [1517, 1607]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["WARNING: The name of this take must be unique: no take should exist with the same name."], "extent": [1607, 1701]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Output Driver"], "extent": [1701, 1716], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The name of the ROP node that is called after the merged take is activated."], "extent": [1716, 1797]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["WARNING: The Output Driver ROP node must be set to render the '(Current)' take.\n    Also, the Output Driver ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["must be specified with an absolute path"]}, "."], "extent": [1797, 1954]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Takes"], "extent": [1954, 1961], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The list of take names to be merged.\n    Each text field can contain multiple take names (this allows for\n    more flexible editing.)"], "extent": [1961, 2100]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Non-existing take names are silently ignored."], "extent": [2100, 2152]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Test\u2013Create/Update Merged Take (button)"], "extent": [2152, 2194], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This convenience button allows you to manually check the results of\n    the take merge: it creates the merged take but will not render it."], "extent": [2194, 2338]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The other button deletes the temporary take (you have to switch back\n    to the Main take manually first)."], "extent": [2338, 2450]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [2450, 2455], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you want to use a single Output Driver:"], "extent": [2455, 2502]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["specify ", {"type": "code", "text": ["$ACTIVETAKE.$F4.exr"]}, " (or similar) as output file name in your ROP node"], "extent": [2502, 2588]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["for each takeMerge node that represents a render layer, name it after the layer it represents"], "extent": [2588, 2689]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This way you can run all your layers through a single ROP node, and all resulting\n    image sequences will be named appropriately."], "extent": [2689, 2825]}], "container": true}, {"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [2825, 2830], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["One reason why there are multiple 'Takes' text fields is to allow editing of single\n    lines ", {"type": "em", "text": ["when multiple nodes are selected"]}, " without changing the other fields."], "extent": [2830, 2999]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This fact you can work with to your advantage (using specific fields for specific\n    types of overrides \u2026 I mean takes)."], "extent": [2999, 3129]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "hqusage", "container": true, "type": "hqusage_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["Usage with HQueue"], "role": "section", "extent": [3129, 3156], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This ROP can be used with the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/out/hq_render", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/out/hq_render.html"}, " node, but frame ranges are to be set up\n    in a certain way so the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/out/hq_render", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/out/hq_render.html"}, " node can break down the process to smaller chunks."], "extent": [3156, 3353]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The following steps are needed:"], "extent": [3353, 3389]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable ", {"type": "code", "text": ["HQueue Mode"]}, " on the Take Merge ROP."], "extent": [3389, 3439]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Set up your desired frame range on the Take Merge ROP (range controls are hidden unless in HQueue Mode)."], "extent": [3439, 3550]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Set 'Render Any Frame' on the Output Driver called by the Take Merge ROP. (Warning: Make sure that none of the applied takes set an explicit render range on your Output Driver!)"], "extent": [3550, 3734]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Set the Take Merge ROP as the output driver for the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/out/hq_render", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/out/hq_render.html"}, " node."], "extent": [3734, 3819]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Render with the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/out/hq_render", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/out/hq_render.html"}, " node."], "extent": [3819, 3869]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This setup is necessary because the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/out/hq_render", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/out/hq_render.html"}, " node requires the frame range settings to be available\n    right on the specified Output Driver (the Take Merge ROP in this case)."], "extent": [3869, 4062]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Make sure the ROP node that does the actual rendering has 'Render Any Frame' set \u2013 if it has a frame range set, it will\n    render that range for each frame-render job created by HQueue!"], "extent": [4062, 4257]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "relnotes", "container": true, "type": "relnotes_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["Release Notes"], "role": "section", "extent": [4257, 4281], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["interface version 1"]}, " \u2014"], "extent": [4281, 4313]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2014-09-17"], "extent": [4313, 4329], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Error messages are now properly propagated to asset container"], "extent": [4329, 4400]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2013-08-31"], "extent": [4400, 4416], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Help card update."], "extent": [4416, 4444]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["older versions"]}, " \u2014"], "extent": [4444, 4470]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Version 0.0.3"], "extent": [4470, 4489], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Added on/off toggle for each take list field."], "extent": [4489, 4546]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Version 0.0.2"], "extent": [4546, 4565], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Merge code rewritten in Python."], "extent": [4565, 4607]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Lifted known limitation of ignoring contents in take hierarchy parents."], "extent": [4607, 4689]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Changed UI to support variable number of Take lines."], "extent": [4689, 4752]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["A Prettier icon. :)"], "extent": [4752, 4783]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Version 0.0.1"], "extent": [4783, 4802], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["First prototype.\n        Known limitation: hierarchical parent contents for takes not included when merging."], "extent": [4802, 4920]}], "container": true}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["Take Merge qL"], "summary": ["Merges specified takes together into a (temporary) new take, then renders the result."]}